## 7. INTERACTIVE COMPONENTS

### Buttons

```css
/* Primary */
.btn-primary {
  background: var(--color-brand);
  color: #fff;
  padding: 10px 20px;
  border-radius: var(--radius-md);
  font-size: var(--text-sm);
  font-weight: 500;
  letter-spacing: 0.01em;
  border: none;
  cursor: pointer;
  transition: background 150ms ease, transform 100ms ease, box-shadow 150ms ease;
}
.btn-primary:hover  { background: var(--color-brand-hover); box-shadow: var(--shadow-md); }
.btn-primary:active { transform: scale(0.98); box-shadow: none; }
.btn-primary:focus-visible { outline: none; box-shadow: var(--shadow-focus); }
.btn-primary:disabled { opacity: 0.45; cursor: not-allowed; }

/* Secondary */
.btn-secondary {
  background: transparent;
  color: var(--color-text-primary);
  border: 1px solid var(--color-border-strong);
  padding: 10px 20px;
  border-radius: var(--radius-md);
  font-size: var(--text-sm);
  font-weight: 500;
  transition: background 150ms ease, border-color 150ms ease;
}
.btn-secondary:hover { background: var(--color-bg-subtle); border-color: rgba(0,0,0,0.24); }
```

### Button Rules

- Minimum touch target: **44×44px** (Apple HIG requirement)
- Minimum button height: `36px` (compact), `40px` (default), `48px` (large)
- Never use more than **one primary button** per view/section.
- Button labels: sentence case, action-oriented verbs ("Save changes", "Get started", "Delete account")
- Loading states: replace label with spinner, maintain button dimensions exactly
- Destructive actions: use `--color-error` background only after confirmation step

### Inputs & Forms

```css
.input {
  width: 100%;
  padding: 10px 14px;
  border: 1px solid var(--color-border-strong);
  border-radius: var(--radius-md);
  font-size: var(--text-base);
  color: var(--color-text-primary);
  background: var(--color-surface);
  transition: border-color 150ms ease, box-shadow 150ms ease;
  outline: none;
  box-shadow: var(--shadow-inset);
}
.input::placeholder { color: var(--color-text-tertiary); }
.input:hover        { border-color: rgba(0,0,0,0.24); }
.input:focus        { border-color: var(--color-brand); box-shadow: var(--shadow-focus); }
.input.error        { border-color: var(--color-error); box-shadow: 0 0 0 3px rgba(239,68,68,0.2); }
.input:disabled     { background: var(--color-bg-muted); color: var(--color-text-disabled); cursor: not-allowed; }
```

### Form Rules

- Always pair inputs with **visible labels** above — never placeholder-only.
- Error messages: below the input, `--color-error`, 13px, immediately visible on blur.
- Helper text: below the input, `--color-text-tertiary`, 13px.
- Input label: `13px`, `font-weight: 500`, `--color-text-secondary`, `margin-bottom: 6px`.
- Group related fields (address, card info) under a single section header.
- Required fields: mark with `*` in label, explain at form top ("* required fields").
- Form submit: right-aligned or full-width — never left-aligned on desktop forms.
- Inline validation: on blur for format errors, on submit for required errors.

