## 8. MOTION & ANIMATION

### Timing Functions

```css
--ease-default:   cubic-bezier(0.16, 1, 0.3, 1);     /* Snappy spring — most UI */
--ease-in:        cubic-bezier(0.4, 0, 1, 1);          /* Exiting elements */
--ease-out:       cubic-bezier(0, 0, 0.2, 1);          /* Entering elements */
--ease-in-out:    cubic-bezier(0.4, 0, 0.2, 1);        /* Balanced transitions */
--ease-bounce:    cubic-bezier(0.34, 1.56, 0.64, 1);  /* Playful, sparingly */
--ease-linear:    linear;                               /* Loaders, spinners */
```

### Duration Scale

```css
--duration-instant:  50ms;   /* Immediate feedback (hover color) */
--duration-fast:     100ms;  /* Button press, checkbox toggle */
--duration-normal:   150ms;  /* Most transitions */
--duration-moderate: 250ms;  /* Dropdowns, menus */
--duration-slow:     350ms;  /* Modals, drawers */
--duration-slower:   500ms;  /* Page transitions, onboarding */
```

### Motion Rules

- **Hover color/border changes:** `150ms ease`
- **Scale on press:** `transform: scale(0.97–0.98)` over `100ms`
- **Dropdowns/menus:** fade + translate `8px → 0` over `200ms ease-out`
- **Modals:** fade backdrop over `200ms`; scale `0.96 → 1` + fade content over `250ms ease-out`
- **Toasts/notifications:** slide in from bottom/top, `300ms ease-out`
- **Page transitions:** max `400ms`. Prefer fade or subtle slide.
- **Skeleton loaders:** `1.5s` pulse animation, `ease-in-out`, infinite.
- Always add `@media (prefers-reduced-motion: reduce)` — disable or minimize all animations.
- **Never animate width/height directly.** Use `transform: scaleY()` or `max-height` with overflow hidden.
- Properties to animate: `opacity`, `transform`, `box-shadow`, `background-color`, `border-color`. Not `top`, `left`, `width`, `height`.

---

## 9. NAVIGATION

### Top Navigation Bar

- Height: `56px–64px`
- Sticky at top, `backdrop-filter: blur(12px) saturate(180%)` for glass effect
- Background: `rgba(255,255,255,0.85)` (light), `rgba(10,10,10,0.85)` (dark)
- Bottom border: `1px solid var(--color-border)` or shadow `var(--shadow-sm)`
- Logo: left-aligned. Primary nav: center or left. CTA/account: right.
- Active nav item: `font-weight: 500`, brand color underline or background pill.
- Mobile: hamburger → full-screen or drawer overlay.

### Sidebar Navigation

- Width: `240px–260px` (collapsed: `64px–72px`)
- Section headers: `11px`, `font-weight: 600`, `letter-spacing: 0.08em`, `text-transform: uppercase`, `--color-text-tertiary`
- Nav items: `14px`, `font-weight: 450`, `height: 36px`, `border-radius: var(--radius-md)`
- Active item: `background: var(--color-brand-subtle)`, `color: var(--color-brand)`, `font-weight: 500`
- Hover: `background: var(--color-bg-muted)`, `150ms ease`
- Icons: `18px×18px`, consistent style (outline preferred for inactive, filled for active)
- Group spacing: `24px` between sections

---

## 10. DATA DISPLAY

### Tables

- Header: `12px`, `font-weight: 600`, `letter-spacing: 0.04em`, `text-transform: uppercase`, `--color-text-secondary`
- Row height: `48px–56px`
- Cell padding: `12px 16px`
- Dividers: `1px solid var(--color-border)` between rows only (no column dividers unless data-dense)
- Hover state: `background: var(--color-bg-subtle)`
- Sortable headers: chevron icon, `150ms` transition
- Striped rows: avoid. Use hover states instead.
- Sticky header on scroll for long tables.
- Empty states: centered illustration/icon + headline + subtext + CTA

### Cards

- Background: `var(--color-surface)`
- Border: `1px solid var(--color-border)` OR `box-shadow: var(--shadow-sm)` — never both
- Padding: `24px`
- Border-radius: `var(--radius-lg)` or `var(--radius-xl)`
- Hover (if interactive): `box-shadow: var(--shadow-md)`, `border-color` strengthens, `150ms ease`
- Card grid gap: `16px–24px`

### Metrics / Stats

- Metric value: `28px–36px`, `font-weight: 600`, `--color-text-primary`
- Metric label: `13px`, `font-weight: 500`, `--color-text-secondary`
- Delta indicator: colored badge/text (`--color-success` for positive, `--color-error` for negative)
- Trend sparklines: `40px` tall, no axes, single color line

---

## 11. FEEDBACK & STATUS

### Toast / Notification

- Position: bottom-right (desktop), bottom-center (mobile)
- Width: `320px–400px`
- Padding: `14px 16px`
- Border-radius: `var(--radius-lg)`
- Shadow: `var(--shadow-xl)`
- Auto-dismiss: `4000ms` (info/success), `6000ms` (warning), manual only (error)
- Always include a close `×` button
- Stack multiple toasts vertically, newest on top

### Loading States

- **Skeleton screens** over spinners for content loading — they reduce perceived wait time.
- Skeleton: `background: linear-gradient(90deg, #f0f0f0 25%, #e0e0e0 50%, #f0f0f0 75%)`, animated.
- Button loading: spinner replaces label, button disabled, same dimensions.
- Full-page loading: centered spinner with subtle fade-in after `300ms` (prevent flash for fast loads).
- Progress bars: `4px` height, brand color fill, always show for operations >2 seconds.

### Empty States

- Icon: `48px–64px`, `--color-text-tertiary`
- Title: `16px–18px`, `font-weight: 600`
- Description: `14px`, `--color-text-secondary`, max `280px` width
- CTA button: primary, directly actionable
- Never show raw empty tables/lists — always design the empty state.

### Error States

- Inline field errors: red border + message below field — immediate, specific ("Email is required", not "Invalid input")
- Page-level errors: banner below nav with dismiss, `--color-error-subtle` background
- 404/500 pages: friendly illustration, clear message, back/home navigation
- Never expose technical error codes to end users.

---

## 12. MODALS & OVERLAYS

```
Modal anatomy:
- Backdrop: rgba(0,0,0,0.5), blur(4px) optional
- Container: max-width 480px (small), 640px (default), 800px (large)
- Padding: 32px
- Border-radius: var(--radius-xl)
- Shadow: var(--shadow-2xl)
- Header: title (18px, 600 weight) + close button (top right, 44×44 touch target)
- Body: scrollable if needed, max-height 70vh
- Footer: action buttons, right-aligned. Primary action rightmost.
```

Rules:

- **One modal at a time.** Never stack modals.
- Dismiss on backdrop click (unless destructive confirmation).
- Always trap focus inside modal while open.
- `Escape` key closes modal.
- Mobile: modals become **bottom sheets** with drag handle, `border-radius` top-only.
- Confirm destructive actions with explicit typed confirmation or named action button (not just "OK").

---

## 13. ACCESSIBILITY (NON-NEGOTIABLE)

- **WCAG 2.1 AA minimum** for all shipped UI.
- All interactive elements reachable and operable via keyboard.
- Focus indicators: visible, minimum `3px` outline or `box-shadow: var(--shadow-focus)`. Never `outline: none` without a replacement.
- All images: meaningful `alt` text; decorative images: `alt=""`.
- Form inputs: always associated `<label>` via `for`/`id` or `aria-label`.
- Error messages: linked to inputs via `aria-describedby`.
- Dynamic content: use `aria-live="polite"` for non-critical, `aria-live="assertive"` for critical updates.
- Color alone never conveys meaning — pair with icon, text, or pattern.
- Touch targets: minimum `44×44px` (Apple HIG), `48×48px` (Material).
- Motion: `@media (prefers-reduced-motion: reduce)` — disable or minimize animations.
- Semantic HTML first: use `<button>` not `<div onClick>`, `<nav>`, `<main>`, `<aside>`, landmark roles.

---

## 14. DARK MODE

- Support `prefers-color-scheme: dark` as minimum.
- Never simply invert colors — redesign for dark context.
- Dark backgrounds: `#0a0a0a` (deepest), `#111111` (base), `#1a1a1a` (surface), `#222222` (raised)
- Dark borders: `rgba(255,255,255,0.08)` (subtle), `rgba(255,255,255,0.12)` (strong)
- Dark text: `#f5f5f5` (primary), `#a0a0a0` (secondary), `#606060` (tertiary)
- Shadows in dark mode: less visible — add subtle glow or stronger border instead.
- Saturate colors slightly for dark mode — they appear muted on dark backgrounds.
- Use CSS custom properties with `:root` / `[data-theme="dark"]` pattern for easy switching.

---

## 15. RESPONSIVE DESIGN

### Breakpoints

```css
--bp-xs:  375px;   /* Small mobile */
--bp-sm:  640px;   /* Mobile */
--bp-md:  768px;   /* Tablet */
--bp-lg:  1024px;  /* Desktop */
--bp-xl:  1280px;  /* Large desktop */
--bp-2xl: 1536px;  /* Wide */
```

### Rules

- **Mobile-first**: design smallest screen first, enhance upward.
- Touch targets minimum `44px` on mobile.
- Font sizes: bump up `1–2px` on mobile for readability.
- Navigation: always convert to mobile-appropriate pattern (bottom tab bar or hamburger drawer).
- Tables: scroll horizontally on mobile, or collapse to card list view.
- Multi-column layouts: collapse to single column below `768px`.
- Modals: full-screen or bottom sheet on mobile.
- Remove hover-only interactions on touch devices — use `@media (hover: hover)`.

---

## 16. COMPONENT CONSISTENCY RULES

- **Spacing**: All components use the 4px grid. No random pixel values.
- **Color**: Only use design token variables — no hardcoded hex values in components.
- **Icons**: One icon library per product. Consistent stroke width. `18px` or `20px` default size.
- **Transitions**: All interactive elements use the defined easing + duration tokens.
- **States**: Every interactive component has: default, hover, focus, active, disabled, loading, error states.
- **Naming**: BEM or design-token naming conventions. Consistent and predictable.
- **Density**: Three densities max — compact (data-dense views), default, spacious (marketing). Pick one per context.

---

## 17. WRITING & MICROCOPY

- **Sentence case** everywhere in UI (not Title Case, not ALL CAPS except labels).
- Action buttons: verb-first ("Save changes", "Delete account", "Send invoice").
- Error messages: specific and helpful — tell users what went wrong AND how to fix it.
- Confirmation dialogs: describe the consequence, not just "Are you sure?"
- Empty states: explain why it's empty and what the user can do.
- Tooltips: one sentence max. No period at end of single sentence.
- Placeholders: examples, not instructions ("e.g., john@company.com" not "Enter your email").
- Loading messages: specific ("Loading transactions…" not "Loading…").
- Avoid: "Click here", "Learn more" (without context), "Submit", passive voice.

---

## 18. PERFORMANCE & PERCEPTION

- Perceived performance matters as much as actual performance.
- **Optimistic UI**: update UI immediately on user action; revert on error.
- **Skeleton screens**: show content shape while loading.
- **Lazy load**: images and non-critical content below the fold.
- **Instant feedback**: every tap/click acknowledged within `100ms` (even if async work continues).
- Avoid layout shift (CLS): always reserve space for images and async content.
- First meaningful paint: critical content visible within `1.5s` on 4G.
- Compress and serve images in modern formats (WebP, AVIF).
- Font loading: `font-display: swap`; subset fonts to used characters.

---

## 19. DO NOT

- Use more than one primary CTA per view
- Use pure black (`#000`) or pure white (`#fff`) for text or background
- Animate `width`, `height`, `top`, `left`, `right`, `bottom` — use `transform` instead
- Use `outline: none` without a visible focus replacement
- Place error messages inside tooltips — they must be persistently visible
- Use all-caps body text
- Use placeholder text as the only label for an input
- Mix border and shadow as card affordance — pick one
- Use `px` for typography — use `rem` for scalability
- Create custom scrollbars that break OS conventions
- Auto-play video or audio without user consent
- Use modals for non-critical information (use inline messaging or toasts instead)
- Rely on color alone to convey state or meaning
- Use generic icons (flat cartoon clipart) — use a professional icon set
- Use border-radius inconsistently across the product
- Hardcode color hex values in component code — always use design tokens

---

